content: Bilateral hand numbness and tingling, and burning pain
title: Chief Complaint

content: She reports bilateral hand numbness, tingling, and burning pain that began around July 1, 2025. She experienced similar symptoms at the end of her last pregnancy, but they are now earlier in the pregnancy and more intense.  She has been consulting her OB, who recommended injections and referred her to this office. The symptoms affect her ability to sleep through the night, even with splinting.
title: History of Present Illness

content: Right upper extremity Skin is intact.
Decreased sensation to the middle fingers
title: Assessment

content: Planned carpal tunnel injections.  She is currently wearing splints. Return to clinic in 3 months.
title: Plan
